# Endpoints


## _debugbar/open




> Example request:

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/_debugbar/open"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->get(
    'http://dev.clearprop.test/_debugbar/open',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
```

### Request
<small class="badge badge-green">GET</small>
 **`_debugbar/assets/javascript`**



## Forget a cache key




> Example request:

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/_debugbar/cache/1/"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {
    method: "DELETE",
    headers: headers,
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->delete(
    'http://dev.clearprop.test/_debugbar/cache/1/',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
```

### Request

 **`admin/permissions/create`**



## admin/permissions




> Example request:

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/permissions"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "title": "quo"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/permissions',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'title' => 'quo',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
```

## admin/roles




> Example request:

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/roles"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "title": "id",
    "permissions": [
        15
    ]
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/roles',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'title' => 'id',
            'permissions' => [
                15,
            ],
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
```

```javascript
const url = new URL(

);
```

```javascript
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "repudiandae",
    "email": "perferendis",
    "password": "sit",
    "factor_id": 6,
    "medical_due": "16.09.2020",
    "roles": [
        9
    ],
    "lang": "et"
}

})

```

## admin/factors




> Example request:

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/factors"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "aut"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();

    'http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/factors',

            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'name' => 'aut',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
```

## admin/types




> Example request:

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/types"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "soluta",
    "instructor": "et",
    "active": "ut"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/types',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'name' => 'soluta',
            'instructor' => 'et',
            'active' => 'ut',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
```

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/types/1"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "perferendis",
    "instructor": "quaerat",
    "active": "mollitia"
}

    method: "PUT",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})

    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->put(
    'http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/types/1',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'name' => 'perferendis',
            'instructor' => 'quaerat',
            'active' => 'mollitia',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
```

```javascript
const url = new URL(

};
```

```javascript
    "user_id": 16,

    "split_cost": {},
    "plane_id": 19,
```

## admin/bookings




> Example request:

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/bookings"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "user_id": 4,
    "type_id": 5,
    "plane_id": 3,
    "reservation_start": "16.09.2020 16:30",
    "reservation_stop": "16.09.2020 16:30"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php

$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();
$response = $client->post(
    'http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/bookings',
    [
        'headers' => [
            'Content-Type' => 'application/json',
            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
        'json' => [
            'user_id' => 4,
            'type_id' => 5,
            'plane_id' => 3,
            'reservation_start' => '16.09.2020 16:30',
            'reservation_stop' => '16.09.2020 16:30',
        ],
    ]
);
$body = $response->getBody();
print_r(json_decode((string) $body));
```

```javascript
const url = new URL(
```
```javascript
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/parameters/1"
);

    "Accept": "application/json",
};


fetch(url, {

})

    .then(json => console.log(json));
```

```php
$client = new \GuzzleHttp\Client();

            'Accept' => 'application/json',
        ],
    ]
);
```

```javascript
};
```

> Example request:

```javascript
const url = new URL(
    "http://dev.clearprop.test/admin/expenses"
);

let headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "entry_date": "16.09.2020",
    "amount": "iure"
}

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers: headers,
    body: body
})
    .then(response => response.json())
    .then(json => console.log(json));
```
